I"*<p>After undergoing <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-manifold-interpolation-enables-first-person-view-sharing">a shared first-person view experience</a>, individuals might feel so closely connected to each other that they feel like being alone with themselves. They might long for otherness and mystery. As Greg Egan mentions in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-manifold-interpolation-enables-first-person-view-sharing">his exploration of first-person view sharing</a>: “Nobody wants to spend eternity alone.”</p>
